AD_COLUMN.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Provider
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Print provider responsible for processing a label request.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Provider configuration that should handle the printing action. The chosen record determines: -Which credentials and URLs are used. -Which implementation class is loaded (via the Providers Implementation). -Which printers appear in the printer selector pop-up.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Active
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Search Key
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A fast method for finding a particular record.
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
A search key allows for a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number originating from a document sequence defined in the "Document Sequence" window. The sequence naming convention follows a rule "DocumentNo_TableName", where TableName is the actual name of the database table (e.g. C_Order).
Usually, company's internal identifiers for various records (products, customers, etc) are stored here.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Api Key
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Authentication token for the external print provider.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Paste the exact API-level credential issued by the provider’s platform (e.g. PrintNode “API Key” or CUPS gateway token).

AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. AD_COLUMN.NAME: Print URL
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: HTTP endpoint to which label print-jobs are posted.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Specify the full URL that accepts print requests for this provider (e.g. https://api.printnode.com/printjobs). During printing, the framework calls the provider’s Java implementation, which posts the rendered file (PDF, ZPL, etc.) to this POST URL using the credentials stored in API Key.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Printers URL
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: HTTP endpoint that returns the provider’s printer list.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Enter the absolute URL (e.g. https://api.printnode.com/printers) used to retrieve printers for this provider. The Update Printers process issues an authenticated GET request to this address. Include any required path, port or query-string; do not append API-key parameters—authentication is handled by the implementation class.
